Members of the Welsh National Assembly fear they will be called muppets
There was consternation among some members of the National Assembly, as a result of a proposal to change their title to Member of the Welsh Parliament (MPP).
The idea arose in connection with plans to convert the assembly to the Welsh Parliament.
Members of the assembly from all sides of the political scene are concerned that they may become the object of ridicule.
One Labour MP expressed concerns about his group, saying that the new name rhymes with the Welsh words "twp" and "pwp".
For readers outside Wales: in Welsh, the word "twp" means fool, and the word "pwp" means feces.
One Plaid Cymru party politician stated that his party was "unsatisfied" with the proposal and presented other solutions.
A member of the Welsh Conservative Party said that his party was "open" to changing its name, but pointed out that the wording of the word "MWP" is very close to the word "muppet".
In this case, the Welsh letter "w" is pronounced similar to the letter "u" in the English Yorkshire dialect.
The assembly committee, which is currently working on a bill to change its name, took the following position: "Naturally, the final decision on the future title of the members of the assembly will be theirs."
The Government of Wales Act of 2017 gave the Welsh National Assembly the right to change its name.
In June, the committee published the results of a public consultation on the proposal, and the renaming of the assembly to the Welsh Parliament gained wide support.
In addition, the committee supported the proposal to change the title of the members of the assembly to "Member of the Welsh Parliament", or WMP in English, although the abbreviation "MWP" was the most popular among the public.
Members of the assembly propose alternative solutions, and the difficulty of reaching consensus is a nuisance for Elin Jones, the president of the assembly, who should be presenting the bill in the coming weeks.
The law introducing reforms will also take into account other changes in the way the assembly works, including the rules for the dismissal of members and the structure of the committee system.
Members of the National Assembly will be able to vote on their future title when discussing the bill.
