Moscow has repeatedly stressed that the $11 billion Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline, which is expected to double the existing capacity to 110 billion cubic meters, is a purely economic project.
The Kremlin argues that Washington's fervent opposition to the project stems solely from economic reasons and is an example of unfair competition.
